    • concretise

      public static Set<Move> concretise(ChessGame game, Square fromSquare, boolean attack, boolean jump, boolean peaceful)
      Generate concrete possible moves from a given piece and game context. Direction: Right, no limit
      Parameters:
      game - The game context.
      fromSquare - The originating square.
      attack - Whether the piece may move to an occupied square. This would result in an attack with a captured piece.
      jump - Whether the piece may jump over other pieces (e.g. the knight).
      Returns:
      HashSet of concrete moves

    • right

      public static Set<Move> right(ChessGame game, Square fromSquare, boolean attack, boolean jump, boolean peaceful, int limit)
      Generate concrete possible moves from a given piece and game context. Direction: Right, limit can be set
      Parameters:
      game - The game context.
      fromSquare - The originating square.
      attack - Whether the piece may move to an occupied square. This would result in an attack with a captured piece.
      jump - Whether the piece may jump over other pieces (e.g. the knight).
      limit - The maximum of steps.
      Returns:
      HashSet of concrete moves
